The value `2147483648` is larger than the maximum value which can fit into a primitive Java integer, which is `2147483647`. Java integers only fit any value between -2147483648 and 2147483647 [-2&lt;sup&gt;31&lt;/sup&gt; to 2&lt;sup&gt;31&lt;/sup&gt;-1, since java int is a 32-bit integer]. To get around this problem, either use an input within range for integers, or maybe use a wider type, such as `long`:

&lt;!-- language: java --&gt;

