&gt; Use factory methods instead of overloaded constructors to avoid @PersistenceCreator — With an all-argument constructor needed for optimal performance, we usually want to expose more application use case specific constructors that omit things like auto-generated identifiers etc. It’s an established pattern to rather use static factory methods to expose these variants of the all-args constructor.

The alternative is:

 1. Keep a public all args constructor
 2. Create a factory Method and use it for other domain purposes

```java
