You are printing the _transposed_matrix_, in the same order as the _array_.

Print after the _for-loop_.

Here is an example.

```java
int i = 0, j;
do {
    j = 0;
    do transposed_matrix[j][i] = array[i][j];
    while (++j &lt; width);
} while (++i &lt; height);
for (int[] t : transposed_matrix) {
    i = 0;
    for (int e : t) {
        if (i++ != 0) System.out.print(&#39;\t&#39;);
        System.out.print(e);
    }
    System.out.println();
}
```

Or, use a _stream_.

```java
Stream.of(transposed_matrix).forEach(x -&gt; {
    System.out.println(
        Arrays.stream(x)
              .mapToObj(String::valueOf)
              .collect(Collectors.joining(&quot;\t&quot;))
    );
});
```

